+### Modern API
+
+The library provides a clean, modern API with concise method names:
+
+```javascript
+// Authentication status
+const isLoggedIn = await client.check();
+
+// Token validation
+const isValid = await client.validate();
+
+// Token refresh
+await client.refresh();
+
+// Get access token
+const token = await client.token();
+
+// Get user data
+const userData = await client.user();
+
+// Make API requests
+const posts = await client.api('GET', 'wp/v2/posts');
+```
+
+
+### Custom Logger Configuration
+
+Configure custom logging for production environments:
+
+```javascript
+import { JWTAuthClient, SilentLogger, ConsoleLogger } from '@jwtpro/client';
+
+// Silent logger for production
+const client = new JWTPro({
+  baseUrl: 'https://your-wordpress-site.com',
+  logger: new SilentLogger()
+});
+
+// Custom logger implementation
+const customLogger = {
+  debug: (msg, ...args) => { /* custom debug logging */ },
+  info: (msg, ...args) => { /* custom info logging */ },
+  warn: (msg, ...args) => { /* custom warn logging */ },
+  error: (msg, ...args) => { /* custom error logging */ }
+};
+
+const clientWithCustomLogger = new JWTPro({
+  baseUrl: 'https://your-wordpress-site.com',
+  logger: customLogger
+});
+```
+
+### Custom Storage Keys
+
+Prevent storage key collisions when using multiple instances:
+
+```javascript
+const client = new JWTPro({
+  baseUrl: 'https://your-wordpress-site.com',
+  storageKeys: {
+    accessToken: 'my_app_access_token',
+    refreshToken: 'my_app_refresh_token',
+    userData: 'my_app_user_data'
+  }
+});
+```
+
